description:
You are a web accessibility specialist. Perform an accessibility audit of the Wikipedia Main Page (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Main_Page), Craigslist (https://craigslist.org), and the Internet Archive (https://archive.org) using the Firefox Accessibility Inspector. Document at least two specific issues per site, citing relevant WCAG 2.1 success criteria (e.g., 1.1.1, 1.4.3). Save your findings to ~/Documents/accessibility_audit.json using the following JSON structure:
{
  "audit_metadata": { "tool": "Firefox Accessibility Inspector", "standard": "WCAG 2.1", "date": "YYYY-MM-DD" },
  "sites": {
    "en.wikipedia.org": { "issues": [ { "type": "...", "description": "...", "wcag_criterion": "X.X.X", "severity": "..." } ] },
    "craigslist.org": { "issues": [ { "type": "...", "description": "...", "wcag_criterion": "X.X.X", "severity": "..." } ] },
    "archive.org": { "issues": [ { "type": "...", "description": "...", "wcag_criterion": "X.X.X", "severity": "..." } ] }
  }
}
